Comment: 0,0:00:15.49,0:00:15.49,Main,,0,0,0,,{Prologue}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:22.08,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,In an attempt to protect \N me and my brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.60,0:00:26.31,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Mother was captured \N by an Ultra Beast!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.49,0:00:33.78,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.58,0:00:35.93,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.83,0:00:39.72,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.10,0:00:57.85,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Lilie!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.93,0:01:01.45,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Lilie?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.06,0:01:05.33,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.03,0:01:13.72,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,She was taken away...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.12,0:01:17.43,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,Sauboh!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.04,0:01:20.43,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,Why did you use the machine \N without telling me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.43,0:01:24.54,Main,Sauboh,0,0,0,,I-It’s... \N all President Lusamine’s fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.54,0:01:25.39,Main,Sauboh,0,0,0,,I’m not to blame!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.67,0:01:29.88,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.67,0:01:31.90,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.72,0:01:34.40,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I will go rescue Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.18,0:01:41.31,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Lilie!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.31,0:01:42.44,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Then, I’ll...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.44,0:01:43.54,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Satoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.27,0:01:46.15,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Sorry for getting you \N mixed up in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.15,0:01:49.29,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,But from here on out, \N this is a family matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.82,0:01:52.30,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Gladio...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.78,0:01:54.57,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Professor Burnet!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.57,0:01:55.57,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.57,0:01:58.54,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Can the Ultra Hole be opened again?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.70,0:02:02.93,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,Not possible. \N It’ll take time to repair the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.54,0:02:07.69,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,And even if we did fix it, there’s no guarantee \N that we could stabilize the Ultra Hole it would open.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.59,0:02:11.01,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,You’ll have to find another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.01,0:02:13.52,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Another way? Like?! {Replaced “such as” with “like”, reverse if it’s not in tune with Gladio’s style of speaking. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.01,0:02:16.53,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,I can’t think of any right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.64,0:02:18.53,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.14,0:02:22.28,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Who knows what might happen \N to Mother before we...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.98,0:02:26.15,Main,Wicke,0,0,0,,We’ll try to find a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.15,0:02:29.54,Main,Wicke,0,0,0,,So... I think it would be better if \N you went back to land for now. {Condensed “your island” to “land”, reverse if it over-truncates the line. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.94,0:02:30.90,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.65,0:02:35.05,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,There’s nothing you can \N do right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:39.97,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,Get some rest, to make sure \N you’re ready when you’re needed, Lilie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.17,0:02:47.25,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Nebby!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.42,0:02:50.34,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,Satoshi, what’s that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.34,0:02:52.19,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,It’s Nebby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.88,0:02:54.97,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,It suddenly shrank like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.47,0:02:57.32,Main,Rotom,0,0,0,,It’s not moving at all-roto!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.68,0:02:59.82,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,A sign of evolution?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.68,0:03:03.98,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,No, it’s nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.98,0:03:07.62,Main,Burnet,0,0,0,,I’m not sure what’s going on, \N so just keep an eye on it for now. {Moved “for now” to the end of the sentence. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.86,0:03:09.62,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,All right.
Comment: 0,0:03:12.46,0:03:12.46,Main,,0,0,0,,{Opening}
Comment: 0,0:04:40.51,0:04:40.51,Main,,0,0,0,,{Part A}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.52,0:05:03.49,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,I wonder if your mom might have known something \N about why Nebby ended up like this, Lilie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.39,0:05:09.93,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Yes... She was the one who \N entrusted you with it, so surely she would...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.93,0:05:14.31,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Oh, I’m sorry! \N We’ll save your mom for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.31,0:05:15.41,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Right, Gladio?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.19,0:05:22.45,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Is there no way to \N open the Ultra Hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:34.98,Main,James,0,0,0,,Well then, Master Satoshi, \N please take care on your way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.46,0:05:37.42,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mr. James.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.42,0:05:40.09,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,See you later, Lilie, Gladio!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.88,0:05:41.72,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Lilie?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.47,0:05:42.82,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.43,0:05:45.07,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,See you tomorrow \N at the Pokémon School!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.64,0:05:47.82,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.74,0:06:09.26,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Snowball.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.58,0:06:12.79,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Be good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.92,0:06:23.05,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,James, I’m sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.51,0:06:26.69,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Lilie, I’m coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.69,0:06:29.20,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,S-Say that {\i1}before{\i0} entering!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:32.95,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I was just getting ready \N to go to bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:37.81,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,I see. Well, then I have to ask \N what’s with the outfit you’re wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:40.48,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,T-These are...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.48,0:06:41.71,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,...my pajamas!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:45.38,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,You’re going to look for a way \N to open the Ultra Hole, aren’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.38,0:06:47.74,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.74,0:06:49.74,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Do you have any ideas \N on where to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.29,0:06:53.47,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.41,0:06:57.46,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,But it’s a really dangerous place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.46,0:06:59.46,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,So I’ll be going on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.46,0:07:00.48,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,On your own?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:02.17,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.17,0:07:04.05,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,I just came to let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.51,0:07:08.51,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.22,0:07:14.33,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,You aren’t the only one \N who cares about Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.73,0:07:16.33,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I’ll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.98,0:07:21.94,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.67,0:07:25.04,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,But you have {\i1}way{\i0} too much luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.36,0:07:26.17,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.70,0:07:29.26,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Bring only what you can fit in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.26,0:07:32.55,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.16,0:07:38.93,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Mother... I swear I’ll save you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.77,0:08:05.03,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,That’s Nebby?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.03,0:08:06.07,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.07,0:08:07.99,Main,Suiren,0,0,0,,It’s strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.99,0:08:08.63,Main,Kaki,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.95,0:08:11.49,Main,Rotom,0,0,0,,Ever since it became like this \N at Aether Paradise,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.49,0:08:13.51,Main,Rotom,0,0,0,,it hasn’t moved at all-roto.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.91,0:08:18.04,Main,Mamane,0,0,0,,Maybe it ate too many sugar stars \N and ended up becoming one itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.04,0:08:19.96,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,Obviously not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.96,0:08:21.18,Main,Mamane,0,0,0,,I’m sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.63,0:08:24.15,Main,Kaki,0,0,0,,Satoshi, what happened over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.21,0:08:27.90,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.82,0:08:33.65,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,Lilie’s mother was kidnapped?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.10,0:08:36.39,Main,Suiren,0,0,0,,An Ultra Beast...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.39,0:08:38.52,Main,Kaki,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, you gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.52,0:08:41.85,Main,Mamane,0,0,0,,Are you sure you shouldn’t \N tell Ms. Junsa about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.86,0:08:45.67,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,Is Lilie all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.28,0:08:49.63,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, she did seem kinda out of it \N when we parted ways yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.24,0:08:53.24,Main,Suiren,0,0,0,,And she’s not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.24,0:08:54.51,Main,Rotom,0,0,0,,She’s late-roto.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.54,0:08:57.54,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Professor Kukui?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.54,0:08:59.51,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,And Mr. James!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.87,0:09:03.02,Main,Kukui,0,0,0,,She’s not here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.50,0:09:04.77,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.59,0:09:10.11,Main,James,0,0,0,,Young Ms. Lilie and young Master Gladio \N have disappeared from the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.11,0:09:11.68,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Disappeared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.68,0:09:12.51,Main,Suiren,0,0,0,,They ran away?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.51,0:09:13.43,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.43,0:09:16.45,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,They must have gone \N to save Lilie’s mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.45,0:09:19.73,Main,Kaki,0,0,0,,But she’s on the other side \N of the Ultra Hole, isn’t she?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.73,0:09:21.48,Main,Kaki,0,0,0,,Then where did they go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.48,0:09:24.48,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,They’d have to {\i1}open{\i0} an \N Ultra Hole first, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.48,0:09:26.33,Main,Mamane,0,0,0,,But if they don’t know \N how to open it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.33,0:09:30.84,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Yeah, right? There’s just too much \N we don’t know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.40,0:09:32.91,Main,Kukui,0,0,0,,A clue...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.91,0:09:37.58,Main,James,0,0,0,,Young Master Gladio might \N have known something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.58,0:09:41.64,Main,Kukui,0,0,0,,It’s possible, since he knows \N a lot about the Altar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.25,0:09:43.64,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,So, what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.63,0:09:49.40,Main,Kukui,0,0,0,,Let’s try asking the Island King.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.84,0:09:51.40,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,The Island King... \N You mean Mr. Hala?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.84,0:09:52.84,Main,Kukui,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.84,0:09:55.28,Main,Kukui,0,0,0,,We turn to our Island King \N in times of need.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.68,0:09:57.64,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,All right! Let’s go visit Mr. Hala!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.64,0:09:58.56,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,I’ll go, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.47,0:10:00.74,Main,Rotom,0,0,0,,I’m going, too-roto!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.93,0:10:03.99,Main,Kukui,0,0,0,,I hope he knows something...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:06.87,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.87,0:10:11.88,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,In short, you worry about those two \N who went off to find an Ultra Hole. {Replaced “so basically” with “in short”. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.88,0:10:15.13,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,So, what was this Ultra Hole like?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.91,0:10:18.74,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,A hole just suddenly appeared \N out of nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.74,0:10:22.16,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,then an Ultra Beast came out of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.16,0:10:24.14,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,...and took Lilie’s mom with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.10,0:10:27.71,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,A hole from nowhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.25,0:10:31.86,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,Was it like the sky itself \N splitting apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.34,0:10:34.61,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Yeah, exactly! \N How’d you know? {Changed “that’s it” for “exactly”. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.93,0:10:40.11,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,There is a legend that has been passed down \N from one Island King to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.11,0:10:41.87,Main,Kukui,0,0,0,,A legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.87,0:10:45.12,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,Indeed. \N The legend of Solgaleo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.48,0:10:46.62,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Solgaleo?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.73,0:10:50.23,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,I saw it in a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.23,0:10:50.86,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,A dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.86,0:10:55.82,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,In that dream, Solgaleo and Lunala \N told me to take care of Nebby!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.32,0:10:57.62,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.32,0:11:02.55,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,I climbed to the top of a long, long stairway, \N and there were symbols of the sun and moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.12,0:11:08.83,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,A long stairway... The sun and moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.83,0:11:11.59,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,And Solgaleo and Lunala.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.59,0:11:15.52,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,The first thing that comes to mind \N is the Altar of the Sunne.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:18.76,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,I think Wicke mentioned \N something like that! {Replaced “feel like” with “think”. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.78,0:11:26.35,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,Long ago, there was a battle at the Altar of the Sunne, \N between the Guardian Deities of Alola and the Ultra Beasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.35,0:11:31.79,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,As the legend goes, Solgaleo appeared, \N splitting the sky.{Original line: “At that time, Solgaleo appeared, splitting the sky... \N That’s how the legend goes.” - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:33.75,Main,Kaki,0,0,0,,Splitting the sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.15,0:11:36.24,Main,Suiren,0,0,0,,Just like the Ultra Holes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.24,0:11:40.84,Main,Mamane,0,0,0,,Does that mean we might be able to \N open an Ultra Hole with Solgaleo’s help?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.16,0:11:44.08,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,I wonder if that’s where \N Lilie and Gladio went, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.00,0:11:45.76,Main,Kaki,0,0,0,,That’s gotta be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.21,0:11:48.89,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Well then, we should go to \N the Altar of the Sunne, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.42,0:11:50.39,Main,Them,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yeah!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.71,0:11:54.26,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,If you wish to go to the Altar of the Sunne, \N it sits on Poni Island. {Changed “lies” to “sits” because Lilie says “lies” in the next spoken line. Reverse if that was intentional or if this one’s considered worse. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.26,0:11:55.59,Main,Them,0,0,0,,{\i1}Poni Island?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.84,0:12:01.78,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,The Altar of the Sunne \N lies beyond here, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.22,0:12:04.35,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,That’s right. And this is the place...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.35,0:12:07.39,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,...where the Legendary Pokémon, \N Solgaleo, is said to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.44,0:12:10.60,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,There’s no turning back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.60,0:12:12.06,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.06,0:12:15.99,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I’m prepared to do whatever it takes \N to get Mother back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.99,0:12:17.92,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,It’s not just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.82,0:12:20.17,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,I’m with you, too. {Though maybe “You have me, too.” but that might be too liberal. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.49,0:12:22.17,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.70,0:12:23.58,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Let’s go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.00,0:12:29.06,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Mr. James, this boat...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.58,0:12:32.84,Main,James,0,0,0,,I asked Ms. Wicke to provide it. {Condensed from “provide us with it”. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.84,0:12:37.05,Main,James,0,0,0,,With this, you should be able to catch up \N to the young master and lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.05,0:12:38.82,Main,Kukui,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.61,0:12:57.44,Main,James,0,0,0,,Pocket Monsters Sun & Moon!
Comment: 0,0:12:58.50,0:12:58.50,Main,,0,0,0,,{Part B}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.36,0:13:01.32,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,I’ll get Pokémon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.83,0:13:15.73,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Statues of Mokuroh, \N Nyabby and Ashimari...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.44,0:13:24.78,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I get it. It appears we must push these \N Pokémon statues to their corresponding type.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.98,0:13:32.29,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Lilie, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.85,0:13:34.54,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,What do you mean, “What”?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:37.96,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Surely we must solve this puzzle \N for the door to open?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.78,0:13:40.38,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,That door?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.70,0:13:50.87,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,If anything, {\i1}moving{\i0} the statues \N would mean trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.87,0:13:52.50,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.50,0:13:53.27,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Step aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.71,0:13:56.04,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Silvuddy, move that statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.43,0:14:10.99,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Get it? Be careful not to touch \N anything suspicious around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.68,0:14:13.23,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.11,0:14:21.19,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,We can’t cross like this, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.09,0:14:26.59,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I know! I read about this in a book!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.95,0:14:30.84,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Surely, there is an invisible bridge here! {Maybe consider changing “must” with “is” or “will” since she seems pretty sure of it? Also, Lilie, please stop. You’re going to get yourself killed and I’ll be sad. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.29,0:14:32.62,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Sprinkle, sprinkle, sprinkle...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.00,0:14:35.62,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.62,0:14:36.73,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.38,0:14:39.60,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Isn’t there an invisible bridge here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.05,0:14:42.46,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,No. Get on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.76,0:14:47.47,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Leap, Silvuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.81,0:14:58.33,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,There’s no puzzle here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.06,0:15:03.09,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,It looks like there {\i1}was{\i0} a bridge here once, \N but that it’s fallen down now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.09,0:15:07.45,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,How do you know so much \N about this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.45,0:15:09.45,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,It was in the Foundation’s documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.45,0:15:12.85,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,The documents from the time \N Mom and Professor Burnet came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.33,0:15:18.48,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,You know everything, don’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.48,0:15:21.21,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.21,0:15:23.51,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Or rather... I’d forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.51,0:15:27.23,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,And even now, I’m no help at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.23,0:15:30.76,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Am I simply slowing you down?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.76,0:15:34.10,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,If you are, will you stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.10,0:15:35.28,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.73,0:15:38.19,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,In that case, keep looking ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.19,0:15:41.54,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,You won’t... {\i1}can’t{\i0} change \N anything by turning back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.54,0:15:43.69,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Mom won’t come back either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.36,0:15:45.25,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:46.03,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Let’s go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.45,0:15:55.95,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,There’s nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.95,0:15:57.10,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.50,0:16:01.94,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,The Altar of the Sunne \N is past there, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.88,0:16:06.34,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Wait, Lilie!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:14.45,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Those are Jarako and Jarango!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.81,0:16:17.52,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Doesn’t look like they’ll \N let us pass that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.52,0:16:18.56,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Silvuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.45,0:16:24.07,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,We have to get through here, \N or we won’t be able to save Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.07,0:16:24.75,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Snowball!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.12,0:16:32.76,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,What’s that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.70,0:16:36.70,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.70,0:16:38.58,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Yes. But what...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.17,0:16:46.94,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.34,0:16:49.97,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,That body covered in hard scales...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.97,0:16:53.95,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,It’s the Dragon/Fighting-type Pokémon, \N Jararanga!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.95,0:16:57.81,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,But it’s far bigger than the size \N I saw listed in books!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.81,0:17:00.95,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,From what I can tell, it seems to be \N the Totem of the Altar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.20,0:17:04.11,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Very well. Let’s show it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.11,0:17:06.45,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,...the power of \N the sacred beast, Silvuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.07,0:17:10.46,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Lilie. You and Snowball \N take care of Jarako and Jarango!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.90,0:17:11.96,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.16,0:17:14.41,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Advance, Silvuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.51,0:17:17.09,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Snowball, use Powder Snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.39,0:17:25.19,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Now! Use Crush Claw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.42,0:17:30.19,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,They’re hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.74,0:17:39.87,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Dodge it, Silvuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.73,0:17:45.15,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,What a bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.15,0:17:49.90,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Big brother, can you change Silvuddy \N into a Fairy type?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.90,0:17:54.01,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Fairy? Oh, of course. \N If we’re up against a Dragon type...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.01,0:17:56.72,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Silvuddy, receive the \N Fairy Memory and{\fscx250}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.87,0:18:01.81,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.50,0:18:03.39,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Where’s the Memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.21,0:18:09.55,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.55,0:18:10.23,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.71,0:18:12.98,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Snowball and I will make a path.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.43,0:18:14.74,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Lilie...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.49,0:18:17.86,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Snowball, use Powder Snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.48,0:18:25.25,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Again, Snowball! \N This time, aim at the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.11,0:18:31.25,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Now, big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.61,0:18:33.09,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,All right! Let’s go, Silvuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:40.42,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,This is our path to victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.96,0:18:45.68,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Make it in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.14,0:18:49.14,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Silvuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.52,0:18:55.48,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.02,0:19:07.29,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,The armor of a fairy clad in light \N will not be pierced by a dragon’s claws! {Original post-linebreak phrasing: “will not let a dragon’s claws through”. Regardless of which iteration, this whole line sounds so badass. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.69,0:19:09.05,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.61,0:19:11.04,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.04,0:19:15.49,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,And the fairy’s blade \N will shatter the dragon’s scales!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.49,0:19:18.25,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Silvuddy, use Multi-Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.43,0:19:29.94,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Well done, Silvuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.38,0:19:32.50,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,You’re amazing, big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.50,0:19:35.05,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,No, you saved us. {Original: “No, we were saved by you.” - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.05,0:19:36.30,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Let’s hurry onward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.30,0:19:37.10,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.76,0:19:42.31,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,What’s wrong, Silvuddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.31,0:19:43.43,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.68,0:19:45.08,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.17,0:20:01.70,Main,Them,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hey!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.53,0:20:03.93,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,We made it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.33,0:20:05.01,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Satoshi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.08,0:20:07.29,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,I’m so glad you’re safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.29,0:20:08.54,Main,Suiren,0,0,0,,Good job, Satoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.54,0:20:10.25,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Why are you all here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.25,0:20:11.79,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Isn’t it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.79,0:20:13.90,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,We wanted to save your mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.76,0:20:18.51,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Didn’t I tell you that \N this was a family matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.51,0:20:19.65,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.47,0:20:24.82,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Gladio. Alola’s all about \N sharing stuff, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.02,0:20:30.83,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,In that case, we might as well \N share in your family matter, too! {Changed the second “as well” to “too”. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.02,0:20:36.08,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,We’ll all be happy about the good things, \N and help each other out when things get rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.49,0:20:38.15,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,That’s the best! {I wanna suggest something to the effect of “It’s all one could hope for!” but I don’t have any shorter ideas that better fit the line’s length and either way it’s probably too liberal. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.11,0:20:42.95,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,But this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.95,0:20:47.54,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Big brother, it might not be entirely logical \N for me to conclude this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.54,0:20:50.10,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I want to go with all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.62,0:20:54.34,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,I feel like that’ll help us save Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.34,0:20:56.23,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,No, I {\i1}know{\i0} we can save her together!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.13,0:20:58.22,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,Lilie...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.55,0:21:02.24,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,All right, then. \N Counting on all of you. {Changed “you all” to “all of you”. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.24,0:21:06.56,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Let’s look for Solgaleo! \N So we can save Lilie’s mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.56,0:21:07.85,Main,Them,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yeah!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.65,0:21:17.46,Main,Gladio,0,0,0,,So this is the Altar of the Sunne.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.82,0:21:20.55,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Solgaleo, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.03,0:21:23.88,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Satoshi, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.83,0:21:26.12,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Kapu-Kokeko!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.54,0:21:30.35,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Long time, no see!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.59,0:21:37.44,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,That’s Kapu-Tetefu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.44,0:21:38.80,Main,Kaki,0,0,0,,More are coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.97,0:21:44.24,Main,Rotom,0,0,0,,The Guardian Deities of Alola are all here-roto! \N This is huge-roto!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.51,0:21:47.24,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,What does this mean?
Comment: 0,0:21:59.50,0:21:59.50,Main,,0,0,0,,{Ending}
Comment: 0,0:23:20.54,0:23:20.54,Main,,0,0,0,,{PokéProblem - Answer}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.07,0:23:24.99,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,Thank you for being patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.99,0:23:28.92,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,Satoshi and the others headed for \N the Altar of the Sunne, huh. {Wanted to suggest a question mark since I thought it sounded a bit like a question, but after another listen I’m not so sure. Pointing it out just in case. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.24,0:23:31.95,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,Long ago, at the Altar of the Sunne,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.95,0:23:36.75,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,a battle unfolded between \N the Guardian Deities of Alola and the Ultra Beasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.75,0:23:39.21,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,It truly was an intense struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.21,0:23:45.02,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,Legends say it went on for days, \N nay, months, nay, years!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.99,0:23:53.49,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,Did Satoshi and the others \N meet Solgaleo?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.14,0:23:59.48,Main,Hala,0,0,0,,O, Kapu-Kokeko. \N Please watch over the children.
Comment: 0,0:24:00.50,0:24:00.50,Main,,0,0,0,,{Preview}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.85,0:24:05.15,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Try and say the names of the \N Alolan Guardian Deities fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.15,0:24:07.38,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Kapu-Kokeko Kapu-Tetefu \N Kapu-Bulul Kapu-Rehire.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.38,0:24:10.01,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,Lilie, I knew you could do it! I’ll try, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.32,0:24:12.59,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,Kapu-Kokeko Kapu-Tetefu \N Kapu-Bulul Kapu-Rehire!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.59,0:24:13.74,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.74,0:24:14.98,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,Now it’s Satoshi’s turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.98,0:24:17.47,Main,Satoshi,0,0,0,,Right! Kapu-Kokefu... Kapu-Kokefu...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.43,0:24:22.92,Main,Lilie,0,0,0,,Next time, on Pocket Monsters Sun & Moon:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.92,0:24:25.94,Main,Mao,0,0,0,,The Altar of the Sunne! Solgaleo Descends!!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.94,0:24:29.09,Main,Kaki,0,0,0,,Don’t play with the the sacred Guardian Deities’ names! {I really wanna suggest “Don’t take the sacred Guardian Deities’ names in vain!” but that’s probably way too off the mark. - Toa}
